5 It ſeemes to mee an undecent thing, that Godfathers undertaking this ſo ſolemnly, in the face of God and his Angels, and in the face of his Congregation, ſhould ſo flight a promiſe made under the eye of ſo great witneſſes. Scitote ſaith Aug. vos fidejuſſores pro ipſis apud deum extitiſse;
               Nodin. Exod. 517.
                and ſurely marriage it ſelfe which yet bindes ſo ſtrong, is not undertaken with much more ſolemnitie of promiſes then this office of Godfathers. And thus much of the Font, and ſome undecencies about that.
